Here are the MSTest patterns for each scenario, using modern MSTest 3.9+ attributes:

**1. Windows-only (registry tests) — `[OSCondition]`**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
public void Registry_ReadsInstallPath()
{
    var path = Registry.GetValue(@"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\MyApp", "InstallPath", null);
    Assert.IsNotNull(path);
}
```

**2. Skip in CI (local GPU required) — `[CICondition]`**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
public void GpuRender_ProducesExpectedOutput()
{
    var result = GpuRenderer.Render(scene);
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

**3. Flaky external API — `[Retry]`**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)]
[Timeout(10000)]
public async Task WeatherApi_ReturnsForecast()
{
    var forecast = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync(_testContext.CancellationToken);
    Assert.IsNotNull(forecast);
}
```
Use `[Retry]` only for genuinely flaky external dependencies — not to mask race conditions or shared-state bugs.

**4. Cleanup temp files — `[TestCleanup]`**
```csharp
[TestClass]
public sealed class FileProcessorTests
{
    private readonly string _tempFile;

    public FileProcessorTests()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void Process_WritesOutput()
    {
        FileProcessor.Process(_tempFile);
        Assert.IsNotEmpty(File.ReadAllText(_tempFile));
    }

    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }
}
```
`[TestCleanup]` runs after every test even if it fails, so temp files are always removed.

**Version requirements:** `[OSCondition]` and `[CICondition]` need MSTest **3.10+**; `[Retry]` needs **3.9+**.
